  "name": "RPlog_Spies_Scalpels_and_Soap_Operas",
  "title": "The Doctor and the Broker",
  "summary": "In the aftermath of a mynock infestation aboard Johanna Siri te Danaan's flagship, the weary broker Kracen Ecks works through repair costs in the pilots' rec-room while a sappy Nemoidian soap opera plays for the off-duty crew. Doctor Lynae Cassius, working at her datapad, presses him for news and learns that the only supplier who can furnish the parts they need is on Tatooine, a man who holds a deadly grudge against Johanna. Lynae, with biting eloquence about Tatooine's miseries, insists on accompanying Ecks for protection, and the two trade barbed but increasingly respectful banter. When Lynae reveals her formidable past as a former Imperial commodore and protege of Ysanne Isard, Ecks recognizes a kindred 'best at what we do,' and notes the two share more than skill: he is a clone, and her remarks hint she has seen others like him. Galen Rourke joins to vouch for Lynae's lethal temper and volunteers to come along, and the trio settles on the Tatooine run as Ecks, intrigued by talk of siblings and fate, bows out for a cup of caf.",
